0 - Github
    create a new repository on the command line
        composer create-project --prefer-dist laravel/laravel docan or laravel new docan --pest --breeze (pest foir test unit)
        cd docan
        git init
        git add .
        git commit -m "first commit"
        git remote add origin https://github.com/decoreine/docan.git // you have to crete reprosity
        git push origin master

    push an existing repository from the command line
        git remote add origin https://github.com/decoreine/docan.git
        git branch -M begin // create new brench
        git push origin begin //push to new brunch you can use git push -u origin {{ brench_name }}

    clone repository
        git clone https://github.com/decoreine/docan.git // clone master
        git clone -b begin https://github.com/decoreine/docan.git // clone { begin ,breeze_vue,breeze_blade }



1 - in app/http/Controller add 2 folder Dashboard & Site

2 - Install laravel-translatable
    Install the package via composer:
        composer require spatie/laravel-translatable
3 - Install mcamara laravel-localization
    Install the package via composer:
        composer require mcamara/laravel-localization
    Config Files
        php artisan vendor:publish --provider="Mcamara\LaravelLocalization\LaravelLocalizationServiceProvider"
    add to $middlewareAliases in app/Http/Kernel.php
        'localize'                => \Mcamara\LaravelLocalization\Middleware\LaravelLocalizationRoutes::class,
        'localizationRedirect'    => \Mcamara\LaravelLocalization\Middleware\LaravelLocalizationRedirectFilter::class,
        'localeSessionRedirect'   => \Mcamara\LaravelLocalization\Middleware\LocaleSessionRedirect::class,
        'localeCookieRedirect'    => \Mcamara\LaravelLocalization\Middleware\LocaleCookieRedirect::class,
        'localeViewPath'          => \Mcamara\LaravelLocalization\Middleware\LaravelLocalizationViewPath::class
4 - Installing Laravel DataTables
    Install the package via composer:
        composer require yajra/laravel-datatables:^10.0
    Configuration
        php artisan vendor:publish --tag=datatables
4 - Installing Laravel Breeze Blade
    Install the package via composer:
        composer require laravel/breeze --dev
        php artisan breeze:install blade
        php artisan migrate
        npm install
        npm run dev
